  fhir:description [ fhir:v "Codes identifying contextual factors that affect interpretation of observations. Examples include conditions or states such as diabetic, fasting, or paraplegic that may be critical to understanding the significance of an observation. This is an example value set and implementations may use other codes or reference specific conditions as needed."] ; # 
